data.enText: a large bird that is usually white and has a long thin neck. Swans live on or near water.
to go around enjoying yourself in a way that annoys other people or makes them jealous

data.chText: 他们周末到巴黎潇洒去了。
data.enText: They've gone swanning off to Paris for the weekend.

tr: stately heavy-bodied aquatic bird with very long neck and usually white plumage as adult
to declare or affirm solemnly and formally as true
example: Before God I swear I am innocent
Airplanes were swanning over the mountains

tr: move about aimlessly or without any destination, often in search of food or employment
example: The cattle roam across the prairie
the laborers drift from one town to the next
They rolled from town to town

value.def: A swan is a large bird with a very long neck. Swans live on rivers and lakes and are usually white.
If you describe someone as swanning around or swanning off, you mean that they go and have fun, rather than working or taking care of their responsibilities.

example.ex: She spends her time swanning around the world...
example.tran: 她一个人自由自在地环游世界。

example.ex: The mother was widowed and had swanned off.
example.tran: 这位母亲成了寡妇，已经悠然闲逛去了。
